<TEXT>
the marine corps on sunday released the names 
of the seven marines killed saturday in a helicopter crash in japan 
the ch53d chopper crashed on shikoku island during a routine 
flight from the marines air station at iwikuni to another corps 
air station at futenma where the craft was based 
a marine corps spokeswoman lt elizabeth kerstens said the 
cause of the accident was under investigation 
the victims who were members of heavy helicopter squadron 462 
were based at the marine corps air station at tustin calif and 
on a sixmonth assignment in japan kerstens said 
the seven were identified as capt michael e bermel cataldo 
idaho 1st lt patrick c fleming bay city mich staff sgt 
stephen r yoder san bernardino calif sgt eric c mau 
bakersfield calif sgt donald r mckay westlake ohio sgt jay 
a watkins spirit lake iowa and cpl jason w chase bayside 
calif 
