<TEXT>
a new airbus jetliner carrying more than 
130 people crashed into a forest sunday during an air show 
demonstration flight killing at least three people and injuring 
98 officials said 
many victims were believed to be firsttime fliers who paid for 
a ride on the twinengine airbus a320 which was delivered to air 
france only thursday 
witnesses said the plane which touts a stateoftheart 
electronic flight system had just passed over the airfield hosting 
the show when it crashed tearing a nearly 500foot path through 
the woods 
part of the plane caught fire 
a control tower official said the jet appeared to lose power as 
it passed over the field in habsheim a village about 15 miles from 
the swiss border 
mondays editions of the paris daily newspaper lhumanite quoted 
the jets pilot as telling a rescue worker i wanted to to 
increase the power but the aircraft did not respond 
it was about 20 meters 65 feet above the ground with its 
flaps and landing gear down when it clipped some trees at the end 
of the runway and crashed in the forest bernard labalette an 
amateur pilot was quoted by agence francepresse as saying 
visibility was perfect 
a 25yearold woman passenger who did not give her name was 
quoted by afp as saying she heard trees brush against the fuselage 
from then on things went fast she said the plane hit the 
ground hard and we had the feeling of an abrupt jolt then there 
was a fire in the front of the aircraft 
flight attendants deployed evacuation chutes and the woman said 
she and other passengers slid down and ran away fearing an 
explosion 
rescuers worked throughout the afternoon to evacuate dozens of 
people trapped in the battered plane the impact broke the planes 
wings and smashed the cockpit windows the fuselage was blackened 
from smoke afp said 
local officials said 50 people were hospitalized it was not 
clear how many were on the jet as there was no official passenger 
list authorities said at least 136 were aboard 
officials said the pilot michel asseline and the copilot 
pierre mazieres were not injured 
initial reports said four people were killed the local 
officials not named in accordance with french practice later said 
they were able to confirm three deaths they said some victims were 
badly burned 
there was an explosion and a cloud of smoke but from the 
control tower we couldnt see said the tower official who did 
not give his name 
he said about 1000 people were at the show and that many on the 
plane were making their first flight at such air shows spectators 
are invited to participate in an air baptism or take their 
first flight for a small fee 
the plane made six flights on saturday 
the a320 built in toulouse france by a european consortium 
went into service in april for air france and british airways it 
was conceived and certified for flight by a twomember crew 
eliminating the navigator 
early this year pilots and flight engineers of air inter the 
largest french airline called a series of strikes to protest the 
use of only two cockpit members in a320s saying it was unsafe 
in london british airways suspended service on its two a320 
aircraft as a precautionary measure pending information on the 
cause of the accident in habsheim which is just outside mulhouse 
and 250 miles east of paris 
air france president jacques friedman said that as a precaution 
the airline was replacing an a320 due to fly to dusseldorf and 
berlin on sunday night with a boeing 737 and cancelling a 
pariszurich flight 
french transport minister louis mermez said a commission of 
inquiry would begin work monday 
the airbus a320 can carry 168 passengers airbus indusrie its 
manufacturer has orders to purchase 500 of the craft 
minneapolisbased northwest airlines agreed to buy some of the 
a320s for delivery in 1990 and 1991 
i doubt the crash would have an impact on our decision to 
purchase from airbus alan muncaster staff vice president of 
corporate communications for northwest said sunday but 
obviously we would want to check into the cause of the crash 
air france has three of the aircraft british airways has two 
and air inter the french domestic airline has one airbus said 
we are disturbed shocked and saddened said airbus press 
spokesman robert alizart in toulouse he said it was the first 
crash of an a320 
alizart said it was too early to say whether the future of the 
aircraft which received its certification feb 26 could be in 
doubt 
the plane has a range of about 3700 miles and consumes 40 
percent less fuel than similar two or three engine jets 
it is the first civilian airliner equipped with a fully 
computerized flightcontrol system the manufacturer says permits 
safer electronically controlled flight instead of the old control 
column in front of the pilot there is a pistolgrip side stick 
linked to five computers that modify and relay the pilots 
directions to wing and tail flaps 
</TEXT>
