home just before 9 pm said hillsborough county sheriffs lt ken 
allen 
lawrence singleton was not in the house his whereabouts are 
still unknown at this time allen said 
singletons brother walter and sisterinlaw diane were the 
only people in the home when the device exploded leaving a heavy 
white cloud the officer said 
while many in the quiet forest hills neighborhood heard the 
explosion there were no witnesses to who threw the device allen 
said experts were examining bomb shards to determine what type of 
device it was 
singleton was convicted of raping a 15yearold hitchhiker 
chopping her arms off with an ax and leaving her for dead in a 
ditch southeast of san francisco in 1978 
the graybearded 60yearold former merchant seaman who grew up 
in tampa spent eight years of a 14year sentence in a california 
prison he completed a yearlong probation and is now a free man 
during his probation singleton was forced to flee six 
california towns after residents objected to his presence he ended 
up finishing his probation in a trailer on the grounds of san 
quentin prison 
two weeks ago he listed the address with authorities as 
required of convicted felons under state law but he has never been 
seen there his brother has said singleton lives about two hours 
away but refuses to say exactly where 
angry area residents have held two meetings in the past month 
