<TEXT>
a partly deaf boy found wandering in 
mexico last year was fitted with a hearing aid saturday and taken 
to an airport in the hope he would recognize an aircraft that would 
help lead to his identity 
the boy nicknamed sabath frequently tugged at the device 
tucked behind his left ear and was distracted by the noise of 
takeoffs and landings 
officials at the juarez center for the development of the 
integrated family named the unidentified boy sabath because he was 
found on a saturday sabado in spanish news reports have spelled 
the boys name as sabat but leticia cota of the family agency said 
the name is spelled sabath 
a hearing test two weeks ago determined the frecklefaced boy 
was deaf in the right ear and had about 20 percent hearing in the 
left the 760 hearing aid was donated by an el paso audiologist 
sabath communicates mostly through gestures and drawings some 
of his pictures seem to indicate he survived a plane crash that 
killed his parents and sister 
for that reason sabath was taken to el paso international 
airport after he was fitted with the hearing aid saturday morning 
officials hoped he would recognize the type of plane he may have 
crashed in but the boy paid little attention to the aircraft 
it was not as successful as i anticipated said luis torre 
a caseworker with the texas department of human services who 
accompanied the boy 
sabath was found wandering near downtown juarez nov 7 1987 
because sabath does not speak write or use sign language us and 
mexican officials have been unable to determine where he is from 
the fbi was called into the case when mexican officials noticed 
sabath prefers american food and cartoon characters to their 
mexican counterparts leading them to believe sabath could be 
american 
officials trying to identify sabath have chased leads in 
illinois oklahoma and france 
the newest lead comes from tampico mexico where a woman says 
her son disappeared about seven months ago she described her son 
as deaf about 8 years old with brown hair freckles and light 
skin a good description of sabath officials are waiting for the 
woman to send pictures of her son said fbi spokesman terry kincaid 
</TEXT>
